tion</b><br>Solutions to climate challenges do not rely solely on in-depth exploration within a single discipline. By breaking through traditional disciplinary boundaries, we will promote the deep integration of climate science, public health, sociology, economics, and engineering technology. We will cultivate a new generation of climate experts with systems thinking, and foster the emergence of new research frontiers and innovative policy strategy frameworks, driving solutions from single-point breakthroughs to systemic innovation.</li><li><b>Establishing a Global Knowledge-Sharing Mechanism</b><br>Create an open international research platform to inspire cross-national research team exchange and collaboration, promoting data sharing, technology transfer, and talent exchange. This ensures that the results of climate science research can be rapidly transformed into global public welfare, making scientific knowledge truly serve the construction of a community with a shared future for mankind.</li></ol>`
